  "text": "Bottom shear stresses. In order to characterise the physical forcing at the sediments, we must estimate the shear stress, r, at the bottom boundary. Estimation of bottom stresses is possible via 4 methods. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] ; and the 'inertial dissipation method', where the rate of dissipation of turbulent kinetic energy (E) is estimated from the inertial sub-range of the universal turbulence velocity spectrum, and the bottom stress is then related to the dissipation (e.g. [CITATION_3] ). The fourth method, which we will term the 'viscous-dissipation method', estimates the dissipation from the viscous-convective sub-range of the universal turbulence spectra and then relates bottom stresses to dissipation.",
